Autolink angles drag opponents using attacking character movement speed, opponent's position and hitbox position to make multi-hits connect with a high launch speed decay in case it gets interrupted but on wall bounce this decay isn't applied and sends them flying https://t.co/RJFYTMN0YI

Opponent position used is TransN bone which is at the bottom near character legs and ROB being big makes it susceptible to high launch speed drags which could happen with other characters when extending their hurtboxes (Plant's down B being a notable example for this)
